v1.1.7.2        19-Mar-2026 - Andrew Leary

                1.  The BBS now has the option to default to a blank .signature
                    for posted messages.  To enable this option, toggle MBSETUP
                    1.5.30 to Yes.  When this option is set to No, the BBS will
                    create a default .signature just as it did in previous
                    versions.  Users are still able to edit their .signature in
                    the Setup menu if the SysOp has that option configured.

v1.1.7.1	14-Mar-2026 - Andrew Leary

		1.  The extra blank line after the user quote and before the 
                    tearline in messages posted from the BBS has been removed.

                2.  The extra blank lines when the user .signature is empty
                    have been removed.

v1.1.7          05-Jan-2026 - Andrew Leary

                1.  File announcements will now include the Origin node.  This
                    will require updating the newfiles template in your MBSE
                    ~/share/int/macro/<language> directory.  To use the example
                    template that comes with MBSE, unpack it from the templates
                    .tar file:

                    cd ~/share/int/macro/en
                    tar xvf ~/mbsebbs-1.1.7/examples/templates-en.tar newfiles

                    The templates have been updated for English (en), Spanish
                    (es), German (de), & Dutch (nl).  Contributions in other
                    languages are welcome.

                2.  The Guest Account option in the user record will now
                    work.  MBSE will not save any user settings or statistics
                    when a guest account logs off.  A user logged into a guest
                    account will not be able to change the password.  Any user
                    setting changes (ANSI, hot keys, more prompts, etc.) will
                    only be effective for the current call.  Once the user logs
                    off, all settings will revert to what the SysOp has set up
                    in the MBSETUP user editor.

                3.  Update copyright messages to 2026.
